  "body": "### Component\n\nForge, Cast, Anvil\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nthe `evm` crate currently contains supporting types for working with `revm`, this includes\r\n\r\n* inspectors (for revm `Inspector` trait used during testing )\r\n* executor (helper abstraction over revm::DatabaseRef)\r\n* fuzzing\r\n* tracing\r\n* fork\r\n\r\nthe executor module also contains the fork and its related types.\r\n\r\nThe main abstraction over various `revm::Database` types is called `Backend`, this naming discrepancy stems from legacy sputnik support, where everything was called `Backend`.\r\n\r\nthe anvil crate also its own fork database-related types that should be moved to evm directly (#1715).\r\n\r\nThe evm crate is rather beefy atm and takes a bit to compile, some features are also not needed by anvil (fuzzing, most inspectors).\r\n\r\n\r\nI'd propose the following changes\r\n\r\n- [ ] restructure the `executor` module: move fork and database related types to their own module\r\n- [ ] feature gate fuzzing + inspectors (only if possible and not too much refactoring effort)\r\n\r\noptional\r\n- [ ] rename `Backend` -> `Database`, to fit revm's convention, however I kinda like `Backend` as it's broader\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
